org.trinet.util.old

Class LeapSeconds

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.trinet.util.old.LeapSeconds

  • public class LeapSeconds
extends java.lang.Object

    Handle conversion of epoch times to and from bases that include leap seconds.

    In the NCEDC vernacular on which this is based "true" means with leap-seconds included and "nominal" means without leap-seconds. Which you use doesn't matter so long as all epoch times use the same system or base. However, if you mix them you will get discrepencies of up to 23 seconds.

            00:59|01:00
     --+--+--|--+--+--+--+--  "nominal" time (no leap second)
     57 58 59  0  1  2  3  4

           00:60|01:00
     --+--+--+##|--+--+--+--  "true" time (leap second)
     57 58 59 60  0  1  2  3
    True to nominal: subtract leap seconds
    Nominal to true: add leap seconds
    See: http://www.leapsecond.com/java/gpsclock.htm Dump of the Leap_Seconds Table S_NOMINAL E_NOMINAL S_TRUE E_TRUE LS_COUNT ---------- ---------- ---------- ---------- ---------- -6.214E+10 78796799 -6.214E+10 78796799 0 78796800 94694399 78796801 94694400 1 94694400 126230399 94694402 126230401 2 126230400 157766399 126230403 157766402 3 157766400 189302399 157766404 189302403 4 189302400 220924799 189302405 220924804 5 220924800 252460799 220924806 252460805 6 252460800 283996799 252460807 283996806 7 283996800 315532799 283996808 315532807 8 315532800 362793599 315532809 362793608 9 362793600 394329599 362793610 394329609 10 394329600 425865599 394329611 425865610 11 425865600 489023999 425865612 489024011 12 489024000 567993599 489024013 567993612 13 567993600 631151999 567993614 631152013 14 631152000 662687999 631152015 662688014 15 662688000 709948799 662688016 709948815 16 709948800 741484799 709948817 741484816 17 741484800 773020799 741484818 773020817 18 773020800 820454399 773020819 820454418 19 820454400 867715199 820454420 867715219 20 867715200 915148799 867715221 915148820 21 915148800 1136073599 915148822 1136073621 22 1136073600 1230767999 1136073623 1230768022 23 1230768000 1341100799 1230768024 1341100823 24 1341100800 32503680000 1341100825 32503680024 25

        public static int getLeapSecsAtTrue(double trueEpochTime)
        Given an epoch time in the true system return the number of leap seconds to subtract to get "nominal". I.e. this is the number of leap seconds "included" in this "true" time.

      • secondsLeptAt

        public static int secondsLeptAt(double trueEpochTime)
        Given a true epoch time (leap seconds added) return the number of leap seconds occurring just at that time. Returns 0, unless the input value is a leap second, then return value is 1 for first leap second and 2 only if its a second leap second in a 2-second leap.
